This would be a really nice feature to support, but it would likely require
some rethinking about the way things are structured internally.

Requested via e-mail:

> Is there a way to put a comment box at the end of a cat-soop solution?
> For example, something like the following (which is malformed):
>
> <question expression>
> csq_prompt='hello'
> csq_soln=r'''
> Do XYZ then PDQ.
> <question smallbox>
> csq_size = '20'
> csq_prompt='Comments on the solution/confusing points?'
> </question>
> '''
> </question>
